public class ProcessMethodMessageEvent
extends ProcessMessageEvent

A ProcessMethodMessageEvent contains information about a message generated from a process method usually via a ProcessTrace. Encapsulates message information that can work in a distributed environment.

See Also:
Resource, , Serialized Form

ProcessMethodMessageEvent

public ProcessMethodMessageEvent(Object source,
                                 String processID,
                                 int level,
                                 MessageKey key,
                                 int messageType,
                                 String methodName,
                                 Resource resource,
                                 String messageLookup,
                                 Object[] args,
                                 Object returnVal)
Creates a ProcessMethodMessageEvent.
Parameters:
source - the non-null source of this object.
level - the "verbosity". Higher is more verbose (less likely to be "listened" for).
processID - a non-null String identifing the process.
key - an arbitrary String key for grouping MessageEvents
classKey - a Class to be associated with this MessageEvent. Allows for a hierarchical grouping of messages. Should normally be the class of the object creating the message.
methodName - The name of the Method.
resource - the Resource used to "translate" the full message text.
messageLookup - the key used to look up the full text in resource
args - the arguments used in a call to MessageFormat.format.
returnVal - the possible-null return value when messageType = METHOD_EXIT
